721031f-a.text:
Lexington Ave., south from, but not including East 56th Street, showing (right foreground) the Ahavath Chesed Sha'ar Hashomaim Synagogue, at the S.W. corner of East 55th Street. This congregation is reformed, and conducts its services in English. It was organized in 1844. Silhouetted across the skyline, from right to left, are The Waldorf-Astoria Hotel; the 50-story General Llectric Co. Building; Chanin; Chrysler and St. Peter's
German Lutheran Church.
February 7, 1937.
P. L. Sberr.
